subanswer.text: Yes, since $129 \equiv 5 \pmod{11},$ we have $129^{34} \equiv 5^{34} \pmod{11}.$ The answer is $129^{34} \equiv 5^{34} \pmod{11}$.

direct_answer.text: Let's think step by step.
